er every 1.6 cM. The maternal, paternal and consensus genetic maps aligned almost perfectly.                                                        Conclusion                                We have constructed the first high density to near-saturated genetic linkage map of black spruce, with greater than 97\% genome coverage. Also, this is the first genetic map based on a three-generation outbred pedigree in the genus                 Picea                 . The genome length in                 P. mariana                 is likely to be about 1,800 cM. The genetic maps developed in our study can serve as a reference map for various genomics studies and applications in                 Picea a                 nd Pinaceae.},
